{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "name": "Ochre-bellied dove", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "name": "Ochre-bellied dove", "latinName": "Leptotila ochraceiventris", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Ochre-bellied dove（Leptotila ochraceiventris）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Ochre-bellied dove。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -918.09, "y": 15.58, "z": -58.36}, {"id": "bird-ochre-bellied-dove-397a1307", "name": "Ochre-bellied dove", "englishName": "Ochre-bellied dove", "latinName": "Leptotila ochraceiventris", "type": "bird", "status": "VU", "summary": "The ochre-bellied dove or buff-bellied dove (Leptotila ochraceiventris) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae. It is found in Ecuador and Peru. Taxonomy and systematics The ochre-bellied dove is monotypic. It is closely related to the grey-chested dove (Leptotila cassinii) and Tolima dove (Leptotila conoveri), and might form a superspecies with them. Description The ochre-bellied dove is 23 to 25 cm (9.1 to 9.8 in) long and weighs about 146 g (5.1 oz). It has a whitish pink forehead, a rusty purple crown, and an iridescent purple hindneck. The rest of the upperparts are dark olive-brown with bronzy green or purple iridescence on the mantle. Its inner tail feathers are dark brown and the outer ones black with white tips. Its throat is white, its breast reddish, and its lower breast, flanks, and belly are buff. It has a yellow eye. Distribution and habitat The ochre-bellied dove is found in the lowlands of western Ecuador and separately in the lowlands and Andes of southwestern Ecuador into northwestern Peru. It is a year round resident in some parts of its range but apparently makes seasonal movements in other parts. It inhabits a variety of landscapes including moist evergreen, semi-deciduous, and dry deciduous forests; lower montane forest; and humid cloudforest. In elevation it mostly ranges between 500 and 1,800 m (1,600 and 5,900 ft) but has been found as low as 80 m (260 ft) and as high as 2,625 m (8,612 ft). Behavior Feeding The ochre-bellied dove usually forages on the forest floor and up to 4 m (13 ft) above it. Its diet is not well known but it has been observed eating fruit plucked from trees. It is usually found alone or in pairs but also in groups of up to five with other doves at drinking pools. Breeding The ochre-bellied dove's breeding phenology is almost unknown. Based on observations of song activity and birds in breeding condition, it appears to nest between January and April and again in August and September. Vocalization The ochre-bellied dove's song is \"a quite distinctive single slightly downslurred note 'wOOOooo', with a clear emphasis in the beginning, then gradually fading out.\" Status The IUCN originally assessed the ochre-bellied dove as being Threatened but since 1994 has classed it as Vulnerable. It has a small population that is believed to be declining because of habitat loss. However, because it is tolerant of degraded habitats, the rate of decline might be slower than thought. References External links BirdLife Species Factsheet.", "shortSummary": "The ochre-bellied dove or buff-bellied dove (Leptotila ochraceiventris) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae. It is found in Ecuad…", "locations": ["厄瓜多尔", "云雾森林"], "habitats": ["山地森林"], "threats": ["栖息地破坏", "小种群风险"], "lat": -2.0, "lng": -77.5, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Ochre-belliedDove.jpg/960px-Ochre-belliedDove.jpg", "order": "Columbiformes", "family": "Columbidae", "genus": "Leptotila", "species": "Leptotila ochraceiventris", "orderCn": "鸽形目", "familyCn": "鸠鸽科", "genusCn": "棕翅鸠属", "speciesCn": "Ochre-bellied dove", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-leptotila", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-columbiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-columbidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-leptotila", "species": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris"}, "expandable": true, "x": -918.09, "y": 15.58, "z": -64.08}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-leptotila", "name": "棕翅鸠属", "latinName": "Leptotila", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "棕翅鸠属（Leptotila）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联10种鸟类，如Caribbean dove、Grey-chested dove、Tolima dove等10种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 10, "x": 395.73, "y": 138.5, "z": 71.63}], "links": [{"key": "bird-ochre-bellied-dove-397a1307__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "source": "bird-ochre-bellied-dove-397a1307", "target": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-leptotila", "source": "taxonomy-species-leptotila-ochraceiventris", "target": "taxonomy-genus-leptotila", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Ochre-bellied dove 属于属 棕翅鸠属。"}]}
